<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 2000 4000 and 8000 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER, GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 9800 - Troubleshooting - ENGINE WATER TEMPERATURE GAUGE,
        SENDER, CIRCUITS AND CLUSTER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ENGINE WATER TEMPERATURE GAUGE, SENDER, CIRCUITS AND CLUSTER</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08245x_8.xml" xrefid="x0824525">Engine Water Temperature Gauge
                    <xref refid="x0824525"/>
                </hotlnk>
                for operation description of the Rear Axle, Engine Oil And Transmission Oil Temperature Gauges system.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Water Temperature Gauge and Circuit Quick Test</title>
            <para>This test will determine if the gauge and circuits are working. It does not determine if the gauge is
                reading accurately.
            </para>
            <table id="t0824512">
                <title>Water Temperature Gauge and Circuit Quick Test</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.19in"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect connector (244) circuit 29A at the water temperature sensor. Does the
                                    gauge read at or below low scale?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(244), 29A.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Circuit or gauge possibly defective. Reconnect (244) and go to Water Temperature
                                    Gauge and Cluster Test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Use a test lead to jumper connector (244) circuit 29A to ground. Does the gauge
                                    read above full scale?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(244), 29A to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Circuit and cluster test good. Reconnect (244) and go to Water temperature Gauge
                                    and Sender Test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Circuit or gauge possibly defective. Reconnect (244) and go to Water Temperature
                                    Gauge and Cluster Test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Water Temperature Gauge Circuit and Cluster Test</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Perform Water Temperature Gauge and Circuit Quick Test prior to performing this test.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0824513">
                <title>Water Temperature Gauge Circuit and Cluster Test</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.26in"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect connector (244) from sender. Measure resistance to ground at circuit
                                    29-G of harness.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(244), 29-G to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in 29-G/11-GJ or 29-G/11-GU* between sender and
                                    starter ground stud, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Remove connector. (73) from the gauge cluster. At connector (73) measure
                                    resistance to ground at circuit 29B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), 29B to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit 29B, 29D, connector (102)/(338**), circuit 29 or
                                    29A, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At sender connector. (244) use test lead to jumper circuit 29A to 29-G. At
                                    connector (73) measure resistance to ground at circuit 29B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), 29B to ground</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 29B, 29D, connector (102)/(338**),
                                    circuit 29 or 29A, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Remove water temperature gauge. Measure resistance between cluster connector (73)
                                    cavity 2 and the water temperature ground pin
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824518">(Figure 18)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), cavity 2, and ground pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open in cluster circuit. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Measure resistance between cluster connector (73) cavity 6, and the water
                                    temperature ignition pin
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824518">(Figure 18)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), 36 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open in cluster circuit. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Measure resistance between cluster connector (73) cavity 10, and the water
                                    temperature sender pin
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824518">(Figure 18)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), cavity 10, and sender pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Reconnect (73) and go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open in cluster circuit. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Turn key on. Measure voltage at ignition pin to ground, to check circuit 28B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>Gauge socket, ignition pin to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 28B/13D, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Measure voltage between ignition and ground pins, to check circuit 11-GV/11-GF.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Gauge socket, ignition pin to ground pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Circuit checks good. Re-install gauge. Go to Water Temperature Gauge and Sender
                                    Test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 11-GV/11-GF, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="7" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">* With Detroit Diesel Series 60 or Cummins N14 Engines</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">** With Detroit Diesel Series 60 Engines</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Water Temperature Gauge and Sender Test</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Perform Water Temperature Gauge and Circuit Quick Test and/or Water Temperature Gauge Circuit
                        and Cluster Test prior to performing this test.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0824514">
                <title>Water Temperature Gauge and Sender Test</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.21in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Connect gauge tester ZTSE-2781
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_26.xml" xrefid="f0824516">(Figure 16)</hotlnk>
                                    and
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_26.xml" xrefid="f0824517">(Figure 17)</hotlnk>
                                    to connector (244) circuit 29A and ground. Set to 307 ohms.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(244), 29A to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Water temperature gauge reads 170&#176;F (76.7&#176;C).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace gauge.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With gauge tester still connected, set to 117 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(244), 29A to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Water temperature gauge reads 230&#176;F (110&#176;C).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Gauge and circuits check good. Replace sender.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace gauge.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
